	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't recomment soldering to old pins.  You need to remove the old lets, so you see holes, and then drop/solder eprom in place.
<br />
<br />Since these boards are double sided, some traces are on one side, and some are on the other.  Even though you verified with a voltmeter, it means nothing.  I've seen verified connections that are good enough for the voltmeter, but not good enough for the actual eprom chip!
<br />
<br />Also, you gotta use good wire.  30 guage single strand wire, which some people use, is junk and should be avoided.  If you don't have access to good wire, take an old PC floppy cable and use the strands of wire from there.
<br />
<br />Keep the wire as short as possible.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


