		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Nerdy Nick wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">if some of my connections take a bit longer to connect on the multi meter does thing mean there bad? ie<br /><br />when x pin is read the multi meter instantly gives a beep<br /><br />while y pin takes a few seconds</div>
<br />You might be connecting across a capacitor in case Y. Or just not piercing through the rosin flux on the surface of the solder at first. What resistance do you measure across Y? What if you reverse the meter probes (connect red where you had black, and vice-versa)?

		

